
[1]shave

   SHAVE, v.t. pret. shaved; pp. shaved or shaven.

   1. To cut or pare off something from the surface of the body by a razor
   or other edged instrument, by rubbing, scraping or drawing the
   instrument along the surface; as, tto shave the chin and cheeks; to
   shave the head of its hair.

   He shall shave his head in the day of his cleansing. Num. 6.

   2. To shave off, to cut off.

   Neither shall they shave off the corner of their beard. Lev. 21.

   3. To pare close.

   The bending sythe
